obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_996  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: AlphaN-catenin is an actin interactor. The paper examines the effect of alphaN-catenin deletion on the postsynaptic dynamics of the actin cytoskeleton in spines.\n\nFigure 2 examines the rate of spin mobility, as estimated using time-lapse imaging in cultured mouse neurons transfected with an EGFP-tagged actin. In the alphaN-catenin knockout, the change in spine length is higher (indicating higher mobility), and in the alphaN-catenin over-expressing neurons the rate is lower (Quantified in Figure 2e,f).\n\nFigure 4: monitoring of spines using time-lapse imaging in cultured mouse neurons transfected with an EGFP-tagged actin. Identical dendrites were analyzed over a period of 10 days. The rate of unchanged spines was highest in alphaN-catenin overexpressing neurons and lowest in the KO neurons. Conversely, the rate of disappearing spines was highest in KO neurons and lowest in the over-expressing neurons.\n\nFigure 5 shows that only the deletion of the actin-binding domain of alphaN-catenin (Fig. 5a, 1-870) leads to an increase in the number of spines (Fig. 5c) as seen for the over expression of the WT construct, indicating that the actin-binding site is mediating the effect of alphaN-catenin on the stability of spines.\n\nTaken together, these data suggest that the lack of-, or the over expression of alphaN-caenin affects the spin stability through its interaction with the actin cytoskeleton.. Experimental description: For figure 2 and 4 and 5, KO data: '...Hippocampal neurons from E17 mice or E18 Sprague-Dawley rats were plated...'\nFor the overexpression construct in figure 2, 4, and 5: no available information of the species of the cDNA." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-07-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_996" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

